# Git...
<br>
  Git is a free, open-source software tool that tracks changes in your files. It acts like a powerful "undo" history for your code, helping you collaborate seamlessly with other developers.Core ConceptsTo understand Git, picture your project progressing along a timeline.The Standard Git WorkflowMost developers use Git by following these four basic steps:Modify: Edit, delete, or create files in your project folder.Stage: Run git add <filename> to move files into the staging area.Commit: Run git commit -m "Your message" to permanently save that snapshot.Push: Run git push to upload your local commits to a remote server like GitHub.